# Issue Workflow

| Condition | Workflow |
|-----------|----------|
| `Modules` overlaps any other **ready** issue (`Unblocked` or `Isolate`) | **Isolate** — one issue at a time |
| `Unblocked` and disjoint `Modules` from all other ready issues | **Parallel** — one worktree per issue |

- Bootstrap prompts: `docs/handoffs/tiktok-mvp-issues-01.md` § Bootstrap prompts
- Locks: `docs/handoffs/parallel-status.md` (module rows + GitHub ops lock)
- Steps: `docs/handoffs/_bootstrap.md`

## GitHub ops (parallel runs)

When multiple agents run in parallel:

- **One agent** holds the GitHub ops lock in `parallel-status.md` — it alone runs
  `git push`, `gh pr create`, `gh pr merge`, `gh pr checks`, and status-registry
  updates on `main`.
- **All other agents** commit locally only; hand off push/PR/merge to the ops owner.
- **Stagger** remote GitHub commands by at least **30 seconds** between operations
  (update `Last remote op` in the registry after each one).

See `docs/handoffs/_bootstrap.md` § GitHub ops coordination.

After each merge, update Status (`Done` / `Blocked` / `Unblocked` / `Isolate`) in the handoff registry.
